<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/normalize.css" />
  <link href="/css/fontawesome.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link href="/css/solid.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link href="/css/brands.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/fluidity.css" />

  <!-- camelCaseToDashDelim(pair[0]) - inverse of how HTML dataset props are converted -->
  <meta name="configData" id="configData" <% Object.entries(configData).forEach(pair => { %> data-<%=
        camelCaseToDashDelim(pair[0]) %>="<%= pair[1] %>" <% }) %> />

  <title>About <%=configData.appName%></title>
</head>

<body>
  <div id="container-about" class="container">
    <div id="container-about-text" class="container bg-gradient cell">
      <a id="logo-link" href="/"><img src="img/logo.svg" id="logo" /></a>
      <p>
        Fluidity is a lightweight, real-time aggregator for serial data, compatible with all modern operating systems. It offers fast, centralized viewing with syntax highlighting in a clean, mobile-friendly interface.
      </p>

      <h3>Key Benefits</h3>

      <ul class="fa-ul">
        <li><i class="fa fa-circle-nodes"></i>Real-Time Data: Instantly collect and display serial data.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-circle-nodes"></i>Cross-Platform: Runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-circle-nodes"></i>Extensible: Easily extend with custom plugins.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-circle-nodes"></i>Self-Contained: No internet dependencies, secure local operation.</li>
        <li><i class="fa fa-circle-nodes"></i>User-Friendly: Intuitive and mobile-friendly dashboard.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Get Started</h3>
      <p>
        Fluidity is free and open-source.
      </p>

      <p>
        <i class="fa-brands fa-github"></i>
        <a href="https://github.com/Constant-Digital-Holdings-LLC/fluidity">Get the software on GitHub</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>

</body>

</html>